ISPF tables are a way to organize data similar to tables in DB2

They are convenient for REXX apps.

Each table is stored in a PDS called ISPTLIB which must be allocated to a dataset.

Tables are created 

Typical REXX commands for use with ISPF tables are:
TBCREATE
TBADD
TBGET
TBSCAN

However ISPF tables are not a database so many of the features of DB2 such as SQL do not apply.
